%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20my%20exhausting%20double%20life%20as%20a%20tech%20worker%20making%206%20figures%20and%20an%20erotic%20audiobook%20founder%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Albertshauser%20and%20his%20wife%20Hannah%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab887b6630eb10385c3c28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223018%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Albertshauser%20and%20his%20wife%20Hannah%20co-founded%20an%20erotic%20audiobook%20startup.%3Cp%3EVeit%20St%C3%B6%C3%9Fel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMichael%20Albertshauser%20co-founded%20an%20erotic%20audio%20book%20startup%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20Hannah.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAlbertshauser%20worked%20his%20six-figure%20tech%20job%20by%20day%20and%20spent%20nights%20working%20on%20his%20new%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20ending%20up%20in%20hospital%2C%20he%20re-evaluated%20his%20work-life%20balance%20and%20went%20all-in%20on%20the%20startup.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Michael%20Albertshauser%2C%20the%20COO%20of%20Bloom%20Stories%2C%20an%20erotic%20audiobook%20startup.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Albertshauser's%20employment%20and%20financials%20with%20documents.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20I've%20been%20living%20an%20exhausting%20double%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20my%209-to-5%20at%20a%20tech%20company.%20I'd%20then%20go%20home%20and%20work%20late%20into%20the%20night%20on%20the%20startup%20I%20co-founded%20in%202019%20with%20my%20wife%2C%20Hannah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20those%20long%20hours%20wasn't%20sustainable%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20with%20two%20young%20kids%2C%20but%20it%20took%20being%20hospitalized%20in%20October%202023%20to%20realize%20I%20needed%20to%20quit%20my%20day%20job%20and%20go%20all%20in%20on%20our%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e69cf5c0-2650-4bee-b4ca-4592336c55ab%5C%22%3EWe%20decided%20to%20build%20an%20audio%20book%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHannah%20and%20I%20first%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20for%20Bloom%20Stories%2C%20our%20erotic%20audiobook%20startup%2C%20while%20searching%20for%20audio%20content%20for%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETowards%20the%20end%20of%202019%2C%20we%20were%20looking%20for%20something%20we%20could%20enjoy%20together.%20Everything%20addressed%20a%20male%20or%20a%20female%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20one%20of%20us%20was%20being%20ignored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20if%20we%20do%20this%20ourselves%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20a%20good%20voice%20actor%2C%20so%20we%20started%20looking%20into%20narrators%20that%20could%20share%20some%20recorded%20fantasies.%20Once%20we%20found%20some%20good%20people%2C%20we%20realized%20we%20could%20publish%20this%20content%20on%20a%20website.%20We%20considered%20using%20Patreon%2C%20but%20weren't%20sure%20if%20our%20adult%20content%20would%20fit%20with%20their%20community%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20previously%20exited%20a%20startup%2C%20so%20I%20thought%20we%20could%20go%20beyond%20creating%20content%20and%20build%20a%20business.%20I%20knew%20we%20needed%20to%20have%20control%20over%20the%20process.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20rely%20on%20third%20party%20platforms%20that%20might%20change%20the%20rules%20at%20any%20given%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20founder%20friend%20recommended%20our%20now-CTO.%20Things%20were%20pretty%20straightforward%20at%20Bloom%20Stories%20at%20the%20beginning.%20We%20found%20some%20trusted%20freelancers%20who%20could%20write%2C%20voice%2C%20and%20mix%20the%20content.%20We%20would%20order%20it%20from%20them%2C%20then%20update%20the%20website%20when%20it%20was%20ready.%20I%20would%20speak%20to%20the%20CTO%20every%20couple%20of%20weeks%20to%20discuss%20what%20else%20we%20needed%20to%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20uploaded%20three%20or%20four%20'episodes'%20for%20free%2C%20as%20we%20hadn't%20added%20a%20payment%20function.%2017%20people%20instantly%20downloaded%20them.%20A%20few%20days%20later%20in%20April%202020%2C%20we%20added%20a%20payment%20mechanism%20for%20a%20%242.99%20monthly%20subscription.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20that%20month%2C%20we%20made%20%24700%20in%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20started%20a%20new%20full-time%20job%20in%20February%202020%2C%20but%20this%20seemed%20manageable%20as%20a%20side%20project.%20Initially%2C%20Hannah%20and%20I%20juggled%20Bloom%20Stories%20alongside%20our%20day%20jobs%2C%20me%20at%20the%20tech%20company%2C%20and%20Hannah%20running%20her%20design%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fab8230b-491f-4de5-8f2b-803001f8d00b%5C%22%3EThings%20grew%20more%20quickly%20than%20we%20anticipated%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%202020%2C%20we%20had%20a%20few%20thousand%20user%20sign-ups%20per%20week.%20We%20worked%20with%20freelancers%20from%20Fiverr%20and%20Upwork.%20The%20best%20of%20those%20freelancers%20eventually%20joined%20our%20core%20team%20from%202022%20and%20today%2C%20we%20have%20around%2015%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHannah%20wound%20down%20her%20design%20business%20in%202021%20to%20fully%20commit%20to%20her%20role%20as%20CEO%20of%20Bloom%20Stories%2C%20and%20she%20has%20been%20taking%20a%20salary%20since%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20parallel%2C%20things%20were%20also%20going%20well%20in%20my%20day%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20promoted%20three%20times%2C%20and%20by%20the%20end%20of%202022%2C%20I%20was%20making%20six%20figures.%20A%20higher%20salary%20was%20great%20for%20financial%20stability%2C%20with%20two%20kids%20and%20a%20mortgage.%20But%20it%20came%20with%20more%20responsibility%20and%20late-night%20calls%20with%20the%20San%20Francisco%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20day%20would%20be%20wake%20up%2C%20get%20the%20kids%20ready%2C%20go%20on%20Slack%20to%20check%20in%20on%20Bloom%20Stories%20at%20breakfast%2C%20do%20a%20full%20day%20at%20my%20tech%20job%2C%20collect%20the%20children%2C%20have%20dinner%20and%20put%20them%20to%20bed.%20Then%20do%20a%20night%20shift%20for%20Bloom%20Stories.%20Sometimes%20I'd%20work%20until%202%20a.m.%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20much%20needed%20to%20be%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c0d1e5b-227c-47ac-981c-767572b3b2b8%5C%22%3EI%20thought%20I%20could%20manage%20both%20until%20I%20crashed%20and%20burned%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202023%2C%20I%20got%20a%20cold%20I%20couldn't%20shake.%20I%20worked%20through%20it%20until%20I%20woke%20up%20and%20my%20neck%20was%20completely%20swollen.%20I%20saw%20my%20doctor%2C%20who%20sent%20me%20straight%20to%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20an%20infected%20lymph%20node%2C%20which%20didn't%20go%20down%20with%20antibiotics%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20have%20an%20operation.%20I%20was%20in%20the%20hospital%20for%20a%20week%20and%20had%20to%20take%20all%20of%20that%20November%20off%20work%20to%20recover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20gained%20a%20new%20perspective%20on%20life%2C%20work%2C%20and%20family.%20Hannah%20and%20I%20initially%20reinvested%20any%20revenue%20from%20Bloom%20Stories%20back%20into%20the%20business.%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20cheating%20myself%20by%20giving%20my%20labor%20to%20Bloom%20Stories%20for%20free.%20You%20need%20to%20invest%20in%20yourself%20at%20some%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20things%20had%20to%20change%20and%20made%20a%20plan%20for%20me%20to%20come%20to%20Bloom%20Stories%20full-time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20chose%20Bloom%20because%20I%20love%20building%20companies%20and%20find%20it%20more%20fulfilling%20than%20my%20corporate%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20love%20working%20with%20my%20wife%20Hannah.%20We%20complement%20each%20other%20perfectly.%20She's%20the%20creative%20force%2C%20and%20I%20bring%20the%20data-driven%20business%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a8e2395-200f-47b0-aeda-edbd04871f9f%5C%22%3EI%20took%20a%20pay%20cut%20to%20do%20a%20job%20I%20loved%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20a%20list%20of%20financial%20goals%20Bloom%20had%20to%20hit%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%20to%20be%20able%20to%20invest%20in%20my%20salary%20as%20COO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20willing%20to%20take%20more%20than%20a%2050%25%20pay%20cut%20compared%20to%20my%20tech%20job.%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20launch%20of%20our%20Pride%20%26amp%3B%20Prejudice%2013-hour%20erotic%20audiobook%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20fully%20funded%20before%20taking%20a%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20begin%20the%20transition%2C%20I%20asked%20for%20a%20demotion%20to%20my%20previous%20role%20at%20the%20tech%20company%2C%20which%20had%20a%20smaller%20scope%20and%20fewer%20direct%20reports.%20There%20was%20a%20pay%20cut%2C%20too.%20In%20October%202024%2C%20I%20officially%20resigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJanuary%207%2C%202025%2C%20was%20my%20first%20full%20day%20at%20Bloom%20Stories%2C%20and%20I%20got%20my%20first%20paycheck%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month.%20I%20am%20making%20a%20bit%20less%20than%20my%20tech%20job%2C%20but%20not%20drastically%20so.%20The%20plan%20is%20to%20claim%20the%20evenings%20back.%20I%20haven't%20had%20a%20hobby%20for%20the%20past%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20looking%20forward%20to%20getting%20back%20into%20video%20games%20and%20going%20to%20gigs%20again.%20I'm%20also%20looking%20forward%20to%20spending%20more%20time%20with%20Hannah%2C%20that's%20not%20work-related.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%20is%20to%20work%20out%20how%20we%20tell%20our%20kids%20about%20what%20we%20do.%20But%20hopefully%2C%20it's%20a%20few%20years%20before%20we%20have%20to%20have%20that%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-working-in-tech-burn-out-hospital-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739356755000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab88a67bb3f854015c7e8e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-working-in-tech-burn-out-hospital-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Working%20a%20six-figure%20tech%20job%20during%20the%20day%20and%20late%20nights%20on%20his%20erotic%20audio-book%20startup%2C%20Michael%20Albertshauser%20ended%20up%20crashing%20and%20burning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(MaryLou%20Costa)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-working-in-tech-burn-out-hospital-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukrainian%20drone%20operators%20say%20fiber-optic%20and%20AI%20drones%20are%20rare%20but%20could%20radically%20change%20the%20fight%20because%20of%20how%20hard%20it%20is%20to%20defeat%20them%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20drone%20operator%20wearing%20camouflage%20holds%20a%20drone%20controller%20with%20a%20fixed%20wing%20drone%20flying%20in%20front%20of%20him.%20He's%20standing%20on%20black%20dirt%20with%20a%20grey%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67aba8cceb4be2fff9a44bff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkraine's%20Typhoon%20drone%20unit%20says%20the%20systems%20are%20the%20latest%20countermeasure%20to%20pervasive%20electronic%20warfare%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3Cp%3ETyphoon%20drone%20unit%2FNational%20Guard%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFiber-optic%20and%20AI%20drones%20have%20come%20to%20prominence%20as%20countermeasures%20to%20jamming%20and%20electronic%20warfare.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine's%20special%20drone%20unit%20Typhoon%20said%20it%20hasn't%20seen%20systematic%20application%20of%20these%20technologies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20once%20they%20become%20widespread%2C%20they'll%20change%20drone%20warfare%20because%20they're%20hard%20to%20beat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EConstant%20intense%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-electronic-warfare-battle-demanding-more-of-ukrainian-soldiers-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectronic%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Russia's%20war%20against%20Ukraine%20has%20led%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20drones%20that%20are%20resistant%20to%20signal%20jamming.%20It's%20still%20early%20days%2C%20but%20these%20things%20could%20be%20game%20changers%2C%20drone%20operators%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fiber-optic%20and%20artificial%20intelligence-driven%20drones%20are%20not%20yet%20being%20widely%20used%2C%20a%20special%20Ukrainian%20drone%20unit%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20but%20once%20they%20become%20as%20prolific%20as%20some%20other%20technologies%2C%20they'll%20completely%20change%20how%20drone%20warfare%20is%20fought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20defined%20by%20the%20use%20of%20uncrewed%20vehicles%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20which%20rely%20on%20radio%20frequencies%20to%20maintain%20a%20connection%20with%20their%20operators.%20In%20response%2C%20both%20sides%20have%20employed%20electronic%20warfare%20capabilities%20able%20to%20jam%20drones%20and%20seize%20control%20from%20the%20operators%20or%20cut%20video%20feeds%2C%20leaving%20pilots%20flying%20blind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOperators%20needed%20a%20way%20around%20electronic%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20first%20documented%20the%20Russians%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-fiber-optic-unjammable-drones-fix-a-big-problem-war-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiber-optic%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20spring.%20They%20became%20more%20prominent%20in%20the%20fall.%20These%20systems%20are%20guided%20by%20a%20hardwire%20cable%20similar%20to%20a%20US-made%20anti-tank%20TOW%20missile.%20The%20cable%20maintains%20a%20connection%20between%20the%20operator%20and%20drone%2C%20ensuring%20the%20system%20can't%20be%20jammed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20it%20was%20unclear%20if%20fiber-optic%20drones%20would%20be%20widely%20adopted%20as%20the%20next%20evolution%20in%20drone%20warfare%2C%20but%20it%20was%20clear%20they%20had%20promise.%20Drone%20experts%20and%20top%20war%20watchers%20assessed%20that%20they'd%20have%20useful%20applications%20in%20some%20environments%20and%20situations%20but%20probably%20weren't%20a%20catch-all%20solution.%20The%20cables%20could%20get%20caught%20or%20cut%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20the%20systems%20would%20have%20shorter%20ranges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20development%20indicated%20that%20both%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20would%20continue%20coming%20up%20with%20new%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tayfun.in.ua%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine's%20special%20drone%20unit%20Typhoon%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20see%20a%20systematic%20application%20of%20fiber-optic%20drones%20or%20systems%20controlled%20by%20AI%2C%20another%20adaptation%20to%20electronic%20warfare%20that%20is%20highly%20sought%20after%20but%20still%20experimental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%26quot%3B%20Typhoon%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20widely%20adopted%2C%20these%20technologies%20would%20fundamentally%20change%20drone%20warfare.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224496%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian-made%20fiber-optic%20drone%20flies%20at%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20in%20the%20Kyiv%20region%20on%20January%2029.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679ce2b7eb4be2fff9a311f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFiber-optic%20drones%20are%20hard%20to%20beat%2C%20requiring%20interception%20and%20destruction.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEfrem%20Lukatsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETyphoon%20is%20a%20newer%20National%20Guard%20of%20Ukraine%20drone%20unit.%20Unveiled%20last%20fall%2C%20Typhoon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrone-warfare-isnt-like-video-games-gamers-make-great-pilots-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsists%20of%20engineers%20and%20operators%20specialized%20in%20uncrewed%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Right%20now%2C%20Typhoon%20operates%20a%20diverse%20range%20of%20uncrewed%20aerial%20systems%2C%20mostly%20supplied%20by%20the%20National%20Guard%20and%20domestic%20innovation%20outfits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unit's%20short-range%20reconnaissance%20drones%2C%20such%20as%20the%20first-person%20view%20DJI%20Mavic%2C%20are%20used%20for%20gathering%20intelligence%2C%20assessing%20targets%2C%20and%20guiding%20strikes.%20Its%20short-range%20strike%20drones%20are%20deployed%20for%20precision%20hits%20on%20enemy%20personnel%2C%20positions%2C%20and%20equipment%2C%20as%20well%20as%20against%20aerial%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETyphoon%20also%20operates%20bomber%20drones%20like%20HeavyShot%20and%20Vampire%2C%20which%20are%20mostly%20used%20at%20night%20because%20they're%20larger%20in%20size%20and%20easier%20to%20spot.%20Fixed-wing%20reconnaissance%20drones%20and%20strike%20drones%20are%20also%20often%20used%20for%20longer-range%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20unit%20is%20also%20actively%20integrating%20emerging%20technologies%2C%20such%20as%20fiber-optic%20drones%20and%C2%A0%26quot%3Bmachine%20vision%20tracking%20with%20homing%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20would%20help%20improve%20targeting.%20Each%20drone%20serves%20a%20specific%20purpose%20in%20missions%2C%20and%20part%C2%A0of%20Typhoon's%20mission%20is%20the%20training%20of%20operators%20for%20those%20specific%20skill%20sets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fiber-optic%20wires%20can%20be%20seen%20connected%20to%20a%20drone%20during%20a%20test%20flight%20in%20the%20Kyiv%20region%20in%20December.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679ce43aeb4be2fff9a31250%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFiber-optic%20wires%20ensure%20a%20stable%20connection%20between%20the%20drone%20and%20its%20operator.%3Cp%3EGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussias-unjammable-wired-drones-arent-end-all-game-changer-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiber-optic%20and%20AI-driven%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20challenges%20for%20front-line%20forces%20will%20be%20even%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20these%20systems%20are%20harder%20to%20take%20down%20than%20the%20regular%20radio%20frequency%20drones%20because%20they%20are%20invulnerable%20to%20electronic%20warfare.%20A%20drone%20flown%20by%20an%20autonomous%20terminal%20guidance%20system%2C%20once%20locked%20onto%20its%20target%2C%20would%20still%20maintain%20its%20flight%20path%20even%20if%20it's%20jammed%2C%20effectively%20making%20it%20a%20fire-and-forget%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiber-optic%20drones%20are%20a%C2%A0less-expensive%2C%20lower-tech%20solution%2C%20keeping%20a%20hard%20connection%20so%20that%20operators%20can%20ignore%20any%20electronic%20warfare%20and%20continue%20to%20fly%20the%20drone%20towards%20its%20target.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETyphoon%20said%20the%20options%20for%20destroying%20fiber-optic%20drones%20are%20relatively%20limited%20right%20now.%20Because%20they%20don't%20%26quot%3Brely%20on%20radio%20signals%20that%20can%20be%20detected%20by%20conventional%20electronic%20warfare%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20unit%20said%2C%C2%A0%26quot%3Bthe%20only%20way%20to%20counter%20them%20is%20through%20timely%20visual%20detection%20and%20physical%20destruction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimply%20put%2C%20that%20means%20they%20have%20to%20see%20it%20and%20shoot%20it.%20The%20Ukrainians%20have%20deployed%20shotguns%20as%20a%20counter-drone%20tool.%20But%20they%20aren't%20always%20easy%20to%20detect%2C%20which%20means%20warfighters%20may%20have%20limited%20time%20to%20react%20for%20a%20kinetic%20kill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20systems%20aren't%20seeing%20constant%20or%20consistent%C2%A0use%20just%20yet%2C%20but%20the%20Ukrainian%20forces%20have%20praised%C2%A0them%20for%20their%20accuracy%20and%20ease%20of%20use.%20Ukrainian%20and%20Western%20drone%20companies%C2%A0are%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-unjammable-fiber-optic-drone-keep-pace-russia-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracing%20to%20churn%20them%20out%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffiber-optic-ai-drones-could-radically-change-battlefield-ukraine-operators-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739356682000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67aba96b6630eb10385c4762%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffiber-optic-ai-drones-could-radically-change-battlefield-ukraine-operators-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine's%20special%20drone%20unit%20isn't%20seeing%20widespread%20use%20of%20these%20systems%20just%20yet%2C%20but%20they'd%20%26quot%3Bfundamentally%20change%20drone%20warfare%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A68%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffiber-optic-ai-drones-could-radically-change-battlefield-ukraine-operators-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sheikh%20Hasina's%20govt%20committed%20%E2%80%98crimes%20against%20humanity%E2%80%99%20in%20B'Desh%3A%20UN%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739356629000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https